comments: Williams (CHA) grabs and holds onto Batum's (PHI) arm that affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Lowry (PHI) establishes himself in Martin's (CHA) path and legally re-establishes himself without delivering contact.
Bridges (CHA) legally contests Harris' (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Harris's (PHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Batum (PHI) moves alongside Bridges' (CHA) path as the body contact that occurs during the driving shot attempt as both players come together is marginal.
Maxey (PHI) gathers the ball on his left foot and establishes his right foot as his pivot, which he maintains prior to releasing the pass.
Williams (CHA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Mann (CHA) briefly grasps Hield's (PHI) arm and then releases, which does not affect Hield's ability to pursue the rebound.
Martin (CHA) briefly places his forearm to Maxey's (PHI) body at the start of the drive, which he is able to move through.
Martin (CHA) maintains a legal guarding position during Maxey's (PHI) drive to the basket and shot attempt and the resulting contact is incidental.
Williams (CHA) extends his arm and dislodges Lowry (PHI) from his rebounding position, which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Hield (PHI) briefly places his arm around Williams (CHA) as the two players engage and disengage during the throw-in.
Williams (CHA) establishes himself in Batum's (PHI) path and absorbs the incoming contact during the screen.
Maxey (PHI) cleanly blocks Mann's (CHA) driving shot attempt.
Mann (CHA) commits a take foul on Maxey (PHI).
Batum (PHI) and Bertans (CHA) engage and disengage with one another and as the contact that occurs as the screen is set is marginal.
Batum (PHI) cleanly blocks Bertans' (CHA) jump shot before making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
